LSF

```json
{
  "application": "LSF",
  "description": "The script uses the LSF (Load Sharing Facility) batch system to submit a job for execution on a cluster. It defines the resources required by the job, including the number of nodes, the number of threads per node, and the time limit for the job. The job runs multiple instances of a command (jsrun) that launches the AMG2013 application.",
  "resource_requirements": {
    "nodes": "4096",
    "threads_per_node": "168",
    "walltime": "30 minutes",
    "project": "MED106",
    "allocation_flags": "gpumps"
  },
  "command": "jsrun",
  "application_parameters": {
    "executable": "../amg2013",
    "arguments": "-laplace -P 16 16 16 -n 100 100 100",
    "number_of_processes": "4096",
    "number_of_threads_per_process": "1",
    "number_of_groups": "0",
    "number_of_cores_per_node": "42",
    "distribution": "bpacked:42",
    "packed_distribution": "dpacked"
  }
}
```
